Comments: Serves the residential area, maintenance area, HQ, VC, picnic area rest room and Dome rest room in a water system with Well #3 (GRSA_W_003). Permit #36273-F and #16400 are the same hole (Well #1). Original drilled depth (1957) was 350 ft. This well was capped due to a threat from nearby leachfield (although WQ problems were never detected) when Well #3 (GRSA_W_003) was drilled. After Well #3 was low-producing (and leachfield was removed in 1983/84), GRSA wanted to reopen well #1 to supplement Well #3. Well #1 was repermitted in 1990 to supplement Well #3. A new 2005 Well Construction report was submitted, but driller just cleaned out the well with sand pump and installed PVC well casing and screen and measured depth at 283 ft. See Aug 1989 letter between WRD and Supt at GRSA (digital pg 116 of docket 001) for 1989 pumping test results. Limited water quality data from 1964-1966 also in docket (pg 125-127).
